<HEADLINE> Lebanese President Arrives in UAE for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese President Emile Lahoud
arrived here Monday evening for a state visit to the United Arab
Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
Lahoud will hold talks with UAE President Sheikh Zayed Bin-
Sultan al-Nahyan on the latest developments of the Middle East
peace process and international and regional issues of common
concern as well as the bilateral ties, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
He will brief the UAE leaders on the dangers that will face
Lebanon after the unilateral withdrawal of the Israeli forces from
south Lebanon as Israel will maintain some outposts inside the
area.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud arrived here from Saudi Arabia as part of his regional
tour, which also includes stops in Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Iran and
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The tour is aimed to rally support for Lebanon in the face of
the repeated Israeli attacks, according to the Lebanese sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
