<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solution to Cyprus Issue no Precondition for EU Accession: European Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- European officials reaffirmed here
Monday that a Cyprus solution is not a precondition for the
island's accession to the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made at the 17th meeting of the EU-Cyprus Joint
Parliamentary Committee, which opened here Monday to discuss issues
such as the political situation in Cyprus, current EU-Cyprus
relations and Cyprus' accession negotiations with EU, environmental
protection and preservation of Cyprus' cultural heritage, safety in
the shipping sector.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session, Co-Chairwoman of the Committee,
European Parliament member Mechtild Rhote noted that the situation
in Cyprus is more positive because of improved Greek-Turkish
relations, increased international interest, especially on the part
of the U.S. in solving the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Cyprus' accession course, Rhote of Germany noted
that Cyprus is the only country which has closed 15 chapters in the
process of harmonization with EU membership criteria.
</P>
<P>
On Turkey's bid for EU membership, Rhote said it is
inconceivable for Europe to begin talks with Turkey as long as
Turkey occupies the northern Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that Europe will only support a just and
sustainable solution to the issue based on U.N. resolutions, which
provide for a bizonal, bicommunal federation formula.
</P>
<P>
The tiny Mediterranean island has remained divided into the
Turkish Cypriots-controlled north and the Greek Cypriots-dominated
south since 1974 when Turkey invaded and occupied the northern
third of the island after a failed pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
During the morning session, the EU presidency representative,
Leonardo Mathias, said "a fair and comprehensive settlement" to the
Cyprus issue can be reached and said that Cyprus' EU accession will
benefit both communities and will be the best guarantee for
security and prosperity for all.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Head of the European Commission Donato Chiarini
reminded that the EU Helsinki summit held last December concluded
that a solution is no precondition for accession despite the desire
for a united island to join the EU.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus, along with Slovenia, Hungary, Poland, Estonia and the
Czech Republic, started substantive accession negotiations with EU
in November 1998. It hopes to be admitted as an EU member by
January 2003.
</P>
<P>
The joint meeting will end on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
