<HEADLINE> France, India Share View on Multipolar World: Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
said on Monday that France and India share the identical view on
building international relations on a multipolar and pacific model.
</P>
<P>
After a one-hour meeting with his Indian counterpart K.R.
Narayanan who is on a state visit here, Chirac also said that
India is one important part of the multipolar world which is
establishing itself.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two presidents hailed the fast growing
economic and trade relations between their two countries and
discussed some future projects of cooperation in the fields of
agriculture,energy and transport.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Elysee presidential palace said the two
leaders also welcomed the coming into force of an agreement on
bilateral investment encouragement and protection.
</P>
<P>
The French president also stressed the importance of an
adherence by India to the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, which he
said would greatly contribute to nuclear non-proliferation.
</P>
</TEXT>
