<HEADLINE> Papandreou, Peres Meet in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Minister George
Papandreou Monday discussed with former Israeli Prime Minister
Shimon Peres the ongoing Mideast peace talks and the situation
throughout the eastern Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Peres, also minister of regional cooperation in Israel,
arrived here Monday to participate as a keynote speaker in a round-
table discussion on "Reconstruction, Development and Security in
Southeastern Europe and the Eastern Mediterranean," organized by
the Economist magazine.
</P>
<P>
Voicing his satisfaction with the development of bilateral
relations, Peres said that the relations between Greece and Israel
had been improving for some time now, reaching their highest level
in the present.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Papandreou briefed Peres on recent developments
in the Cyprus problem and Greek-Turkish relations.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Greece was ready to contribute in any way
it could to the Middle East peace process, a reference to the
Athens-sponsored conferences in recent years near the capital to
bring together Israeli and Palestinian opinion-makers and
personalities.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit here, Pere is also expected to meet
with Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
