<HEADLINE> Romanian Export Hits Record High in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Romania in February 2000
reported 837 million U.S. dollars in export trade, the highest
record figure over the decade, showed the official statistics
released here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Export in the second month of the year went up by 20.6 percent
on January, 2000, 34 percent on February, 1999, and 18.1 percent
on the 1999 average.
</P>
<P>
Garment contributed significantly to the export trade in
February 2000, 19.0 percent, followed by cast iron, iron and steel,
footwear,fuel and mineral oils, machinery, electric equipment,
knitwear,furniture, aluminum and by-products, a total of 69.1
percent of export figure.
</P>
<P>
Romania continues to export products subject to a small VAT and
an increasing volume of highly processed goods.
</P>
<P>
Export-bound merchandise includes labour-intensive products
such as components and accessories for computers, bearings,
chemical fertilizers, electric and motors and generators.
</P>
<P>
Italy in the first two months of this year imported 23.3
percent of Romania's export, Germany 17.0 percent, the Great
Britain 6.0 percent, France 6.0 percent, Turkey 5.8 percent, the
Netherlands, Greece and Hungary 3.2 percent each, the United
States 2.9 percent, Austria 2.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
