<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania, One of Main Destinations for EBRD Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Romania represents the biggest
investment portfolio after Russia for the European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development (EBRD), with as many as 55 projects
worth 1.45 million euros outlined so far, the official Rompres
news agency Monday quoted EBRD representative Juan Gamecho as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"There is no other country to receive a larger sum of money per
capita, a fact which stands proof for our trust in Romania,"
Gamecho stated.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD's net portfolio in Romania amounts to 1.28 billion
euros at which are added another 175 million euros as direct
investment.
</P>
<P>
"We want to increase the number of direct investments as we
want to acquire as much as possible in the Romanian economy," the
EBRD representative stressed.
</P>
<P>
The main fields the EBRD invested in are telecommunications,
with around 180 million U.S. dollars, and the transport and
financial sectors as well as city projects regarding water, gas
and electric energy distribution.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD grants convertible credits to developing companies,
the reimbursement period being up to seven years.
</P>
<P>
"We can lend initially a sum of money and after the company is
privatized, we can turn the credit in investment in equipment and
thus the company will have nothing more to pay because we become
partners," Gamecho said.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD wants to increase the volume of its investments in the
Romanian economy by half a billion euros until 2002, when its
shareholders' General Assembly takes place in Bucharest.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD is interested in the last privatization and
restructuring program of the State Ownership Fund, infrastructure
projects, small and medium-sized companies and industry, Romania's
biggest source for jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
