<HEADLINE> Colombian Air Force Destroys 2 Brazilian Jets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's air force has destroyed
two light aircraft with Brazilian registration that entered the
country with weapons guerrillas were going to pay with cocaine,
said military authorities.
</P>
<P>
Commander of the Colombian Air Force (FAC) General Hector
Fabio Velasco said Monday that the Brazilian airplanes were
destroyed while they were carrying out illegal flights on
Colombian territory.
</P>
<P>
The action happened in Guainia department jungles, bordering
Brazil and Venezuela, Velasco disclosed, but didn't specify the
date of events.
</P>
<P>
According to the FAC, the light aircraft carried loads of
weapons for Colombian guerrillas and on their return flights
transported cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
