<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Develop Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Prime Minister
Frederick Sumaye said on Monday that his government is committed
to the development of capital markets.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an exhibition to mark the second anniversary of the
Dar es Salaam Stock Exchange (DSE), the premier said DSE is one of
the outcomes of the government's policy of economic reform, in
which market liberalization and privatization are key components.
</P>
<P>
Since it started trading operation two years ago, the sole
stock market in Tanzania has attracted some 30,000 shareholders to
invest in four listed companies.
</P>
<P>
According to the premier, the government has taken a number of
measures to support DSE by providing fiscal incentives and
completely removing capital gains tax and stamp duty. 
