<HEADLINE> Iran, Yemen Can Promote Regional Security: Khatami </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
said here on Monday that Iran and Yemen could effectively
contribute to regional security through close cooperation.
</P>
<P>
As the two countries are enjoying highly sensitive strategic
positions in the Middle East, cooperation between Iran and Yemen
can effectively contribute to security and stability of the region,
Khatami told a joint press conference with his visiting Yemeni
counterpart Ali Abdullah Saleh.
</P>
<P>
Khatami stressed that security would be established when
regional states help each other based on mutual respect and free
from any interference in each other's internal affairs, the Islamic
Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
He also reiterated Iran's opposition to foreign intervention in
regional affairs, noting that regional states must rely on their
own capabilities without resorting to foreigners, whose presence
runs counter to the regional security.
</P>
<P>
Regional states should protect security not only for themselves
but for the world, Khatami said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Iran is ready to cooperate with Yemen in all
fields, hailing that unity between two Yemens in 1990 is a great
success for the Yemeni nation and an important event for the entire
region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that a high-ranking delegation from Iran would
take part in ceremonies and festivities marking unification of
North Yemen and South Yemen on May 22.
</P>
<P>
Saleh, for his part, hoped that following his visit to Tehran
several cooperation agreements would reach with Iranians officials
so as to further expand bilateral relations, IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Fisheries, sea, ground and air transportation and housing are
among fields where Iran and Yemen may have good cooperation with
each other, the Yemeni president pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Saleh arrived here Monday afternoon with a 90-member delegation
comprising government ministers and other senior officials.
</P>
