<HEADLINE> U.N.to Host Bretton Woods Finance Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 17(Xinhua) -- For the third year in a row,
finance ministers, departing from the spring meeting of the World
Bank and International Monetary Fund, will meet with the U.N.
Economic and Social Council(ECOSOC) at U.N.Headquarters in New
York Tuesday on international financial stability.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting is designed to allow a free-flowing
dialogue between high-level participants from ECOSOC member
countries and a panel of finance ministers who were present at the
Bank/Fund spring meetings.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. General Assembly recommended in its resolution that
the main theme of the year 2000 ECOSOC-Bretton Woods meeting would
cover means to achieve a strengthened and more stable
international financial system and economic and social equity in
the global economy.
</P>
<P>
The first meeting of Bretton Woods with ECOSOC, in 1998, took
place against the backdrop of worldwide financial crisis. Last
year's meeting addressed the functioning of international
financial market and prospects for the availability of sufficient
resources for global development needs.
</P>
<P>
The discussion this year have added relevance in light of a
commitment made by the U.N. General Assembly to hold an
intergovernmental event at the ministerial level, in the year 2001,
on the theme of "financing for development".  
</P>
</TEXT>
