<HEADLINE> France Publishes Report on Robbed Jewish Properties in Holocaust </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The mission of study on the robbery of Jews in France, presided
by Jean Matteoli, said that among properties robbed were banking
accounts, enterprises and properties and properties of Jews
arrested and sent to concentration camps in France.
</P>
<P>
The report said that from 90 to 95 percent of these properties
have been returned to their owners since 1945.
</P>
<P>
It also said that besides the robbery by the French state, the
German occupying forces also took many Jewish properties including
objects of art and properties of high value deposited in the banks.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Jewish properties robbed by the Nazis have been
returned by Germany since 1957, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Among the estimated 100,000 objects of art robbed by the Nazis,
61,000 have been returned to France and 45,000 of them to their
original owners, said the report.
</P>
<P>
However, 2,000 paintings believed to be robbed Jewish
properties still are displayed in national museums across France,
it said.
</P>
<P>
The French Communist parliament group Monday also proposed the
making of a law aimed at ``fully compensating the victims of the
robbery by the Nazis and the French state'' during World War II.
</P>
</TEXT>
