with the Lesotho government, the staff of Lesotho's Independent
Electoral Commission (IEC), the Interim Political Authority and
the donor community to collect impressions from them on a
realistic timetable for the holding of the new elections.
</P>
<P>
They will present their preliminary report to the Commonwealth
 Secretariat and the SADC before presenting it to the Lesotho
government.
</P>
<P>
After the political crisis in Lesotho arising from the disputed
May 1998 general election results, it was agreed that new
elections should be held within 18 months from November 16, 1998.
</P>
<P>
But Elklit said: "The time remaining is so short that under no
 circumstances can general elections be held on or before May 16."
</P>
<P>
He added that a further drawback is the fact that the
newly-appointed members of the IEC has not yet been sworn in.
