<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Leaves Egypt After Meeting with Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALEXANDRIA (Egypt), April 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin left this Mediterranean port city of Egypt on Monday for Tel
Aviv of Israel after meeting with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
During his one-day stay here, Jiang Zemin and Mubarak held talks
on the bilateral relations and international and regional issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang expressed confidence in the further development
of the deeply-rooted relations between China and Egypt. He
summarized the bilateral ties as mutual understanding, deep
friendship and overall cooperation.
</P>
<P>
President Mubarak highly appreciated the development of the
Egyptian-Chinese relations. He spoke highly of the great
achievements of China's reform and opening policy, voicing belief
that the two countries will surely have broad areas of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier Qian Qichen, State Councillor Wu Yi and
other members of Jiang's entourage left Alexandria together with
the president. Egyptian Minister of Economy and Foreign Trade
Youssef Boutros Ghali and other Egyptian government officials saw
President Jiang off at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin is on a five-nation tour including Israel,
Palestine, Turkey, Greece and South Africa. He had visited
Palestine and arrived here earlier in the morning from Tel Aviv for
a special meeting with Mubarak. He is going back to Tel Aviv to
continue his visit in Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
