<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian PM Arrives in Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien arrived here Monday afternoon for a two-day official visit
to Syria at the invitation of his Syrian counterpart Mohammed
Mustafa Miro.
</P>
<P>
It is the first visit by a Canadian top level official to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Chretien was received at the Damascus International Airport by
Miro and Syrian Foreign Minister Faruk Shareh.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Chretien will hold talks with Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad and Miro on the situation in the Middle
East , the Syrian-Israeli peace talks and the bilateral ties in
different areas.
</P>
<P>
The visit is part of Chretien's Middle East tour that started on
April 8 and will last until April 19. The trip has taken him to
Israel, the Palestinian self-rule areas, Egypt, Lebanon and Jordan
and will also take him to Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Canada is a participant of the U.N. peace-keeping mission on the
Israeli-occupied Golan Heights which Israel captured from Syria in
the 1967 Middle East war. The 190-strong mission, including 11
Canadian soldiers, is monitoring the truce between Syria and
Israel.
</P>
</TEXT>
