<HEADLINE> British Foreign Secretary to Visit Nepal Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook will pay an official visit to Nepal on April 20-21 at the
invitation of Nepalese Foreign Minister Chakra Bastola.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued here Monday by the Foreign
Ministry, King Birendra and Prime Minister G.P. Koirala will meet
with him and Foreign Minister Chakra Bastola and Cook will hold
official talks.
</P>
<P>
Cook will discuss with his Nepalese counterpart the need for
Nepal to continue its efforts of moving from an aid-dependent
nation to a thriving business-friendly one.
</P>
<P>
Nepal heavily depends on donor countries for its development
projects. About 60 percent of its development fund come from
donors.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss issues of the ultra-leftist guerrillas,
who started armed activities in 1996. So far about 1,300 people,
including police, guerrillas and civilians have been killed in
clashes between police and guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
