<HEADLINE> Sensex Declines Sharply on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A record downslide in the Nasdaq Composite Index and the Dow
Jones Industrial Averages that plunged by 356.69 points and 616.23
points respectively last Friday sent stocks all over the world
reeling at the beginning of the sessions Monday.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index closed at 4,880.71 as against
last Thursday's close of 5,172.13, netting a loss of 291.42 points
or 5.63 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index also nose-dived by 169.28 points to 2,650.96
from the previous close of 2,820.24.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted sharply down at
567.81 and 216.57 compared with last weekend's close of 603.25 and
230.14 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index tumbled by 103.75 points to 1,720.56 from the
previous close of 1,824.31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
