<HEADLINE> Indian Parliament Resumes Budget Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soon after the resumption of the budget session, some members
of the parliament accused the government of "bypassing" the
Parliament in deciding to hike the prices of kerosene and cooking
gas during the session's recess, the PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Leader of the Opposition, Congress President Sonia Gandhi, also
said that the hike in the administered prices of cooking gas,
kerosene, urea, wheat and rice had caused "immense hardships" to
the poor, the middle class and small and medium farmers.
</P>
<P>
Congress members in the parliament then staged a walk-out.
However, the government virtually ruled out any rollback of the
hike in the prices of petroleum products, the PTI said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
