<HEADLINE> Daily Non-stop Flights Offered between Toronto, Mexico City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Daily non-stop flights are being
offered between Toronto and Mexico City, said a news release from
Toronto Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mexicana Airlines announced that it has increased the frequency
of its non-stop flight between the two North American cities from
thrice weekly to a daily operation, said the news release.
</P>
<P>
With the inauguration of Air Canada's daily non-stop service,
both airlines now offer a total of 14 flights per week, according
to the release.
</P>
<P>
On a code-share basis, either carrier has access to sell each
other through its reservations system.
</P>
<P>
Mexicana and Air Canada also enable travelers to go beyond
Mexicana's hub in Mexico City and beyond Air Canada's hub in
Toronto, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Mexicana's flights will operate using Airbus A-320 equipment,
offering Executive Class and Tourist Class. Air Canada's will
operate using Airbus A-319 equipment, also offering Executive
Class and Hospitality Service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
