<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Observers Invited to Monitor Zimbabwean Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe unreservedly
invites anyone who wants to observe its coming general election to
do so, Zimbabwean Parliament Speaker Cyril Ndebele said in Cape
Town on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean government wants the election process to be as
transparent as possible because this is the basis of its
parliament's legitimacy, he told a Southern African Development
Community (SADC) Parliamentary Forum in South African National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
In terms of Zimbabwe's constitution, the poll has to be held
within four months after Zimbabwean parliament was dissolved on
April 13.
</P>
<P>
The delimitation board said it needs at least three months to
do its work, but the relevant government officials believed it can
be done sooner, Ndebele said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that his country supports all initiatives of the forum
to observe elections in the SADC region and has participated in
such teams in other countries.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, South African National Assembly
Speaker and chairwoman of the parliamentary forum Frene Ginwala
has urged the SADC countries to send observers to all elections in
the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
