<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Policeman Remains in Coma from Lecce Fans Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A policeman was still in coma but in
a stable condition after surgery on a severe head injury in Bari,
Italy, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Luigi Schena was hit by a missile thrown by Lecce soccer fans
on a train when the fans returned from Lecce's Serie A match
against Bari on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The object, which is believed to be an ash tray ripped from a
train carriage, perforated Schena's skull. 
</P>
</TEXT>
