<HEADLINE> PLA Troops to Wear New Shirts, Berets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The army, navy and air forces of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army will wear new shirts and
berets from May 1.
</P>
<P>
According to the PLA's General Logistics Department, the long
and short-sleeved shirts will replace the 1987 ones.
</P>
<P>
The shirts and berets have been used on a trial basis in the
PLA troops stationed in Hong Kong and Macao, and proved to be very
comfortable.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that this will be the first time that all PLA
servicemen will wear berets.
</P>
<P>
The woolen dark palm green berets are for the ground forces,
the dark navy blue ones are for the navy and the dark blue berets
are for the air force. 
</P>
