<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Arrives for Visit to Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
arrived here Monday afternoon with a 90-member delegation for a
three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Saleh said that he will confer with Iranian
supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei and President Mohammad
Khatami on bilateral and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that Saleh will also put the territorial dispute
between Iran and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) on the agenda of
his talks with Iranian leaders. Before leaving for Tehran, he made
a telephone call to his UAE counterpart Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan al
Nahayyan, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
Iran took over the three southern Gulf islands of Abu Mussa, the
Greater and Lesser Tunbs after the British forces withdrew from the
region in 1971.
</P>
<P>
The UAE has repeatedly called for international arbitration on
the sovereignty of the islands, but Iran has insisted that the
islands are an integral part of its territory.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency said that Saleh and Khatami are
expected to sign agreements on trade, security and cultural
affairs. 
</P>
