<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Index Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The key 100-index of Karachi
stocks Monday reversed the bearish tone on Monday morning and
closed 2.78 points higher at 1,970.05 points, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Affected by slump in American stock markets, Karachi market
opened on Monday morning with a bearish tone with a loss of 10.82
points pulling down the index to 1,956.08 in the opening session.
</P>
<P>
However, the index managed to cover the negative mileage of
morning in the afternoon session and rose to 1,970.56 points at
the close.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 268 active scrips, 130 gains, 90 lost grounds while
48 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
