<HEADLINE> Henan Province Cliches Deals with Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua)-- Central China's Henan Province
signed over 300 million US dollar worth of contracts with overseas
investors today.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-five projects will include infrastructure, high
technology, industrial manufacturing, real estate and tourism. The
investors are mainly from the Unites States, Japan, Britain,
Canada, Singapore, the Republic of Korea and Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan regions.
</P>
<P>
The deals were signed in a trade promotion conference, attended
by over 1,200 businessmen from over 40 countries. 
</P>
