<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Adopts Business Feedback Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive body of the European Union (EU) said Monday that it has
adopted a business feedback mechanism to ensure that future policy-
making takes into account practical business experience in EU
internal markets.
</P>
<P>
New initiatives, queries -- at least 20,000 a year -- covering
sectors of public procurement, technical harmonization, e-commerce,
intellectual property rights, and environmental regulations from
companies to 41 European Information Centers (EICs), will be
collected and analyzed.
</P>
<P>
The results of analysis, including the review of the internal
market strategy, will be available online.
</P>
<P>
The 41 EICs, selected from 300 such centers in all 15 EU
members, will provide information, advice and assistance to EU
businesses.
</P>
<P>
The feedback mechanism is part of the European Commission's
plans for electronic feedback that will cover the full range of EU
activities, in addition to other mechanisms to simplify and
improve EU internal market rules. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
