<HEADLINE> EU to Provide Emergency Food Aid for Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive body of the European Union (EU), said Monday that it has
cleared funding worth two million euros (some 1.92 million U.S.
dollars for emergency food aid for Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The aid will enable the International Committee of the Red
Cross to bring supplementary food rations to those most severely
affected by a recent drought in the African country.
</P>
<P>
This supplementary food ration of oil and UNIMIX, a fortified
blend of soya and cornmeal, will be used in an emergency program
in four districts of southern Ethiopia to prevent the nutritional
status of some 181,000 people from worsening.
</P>
<P>
The special food ration for those worst affected by the drought
is part of the EU's overall plan to word off famine in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Separately, it is making bulk food aid of 432,526 tons
available for this year, with another 110,000 tons due to arrive
at the beginning of 2001, the European Commission said in a
statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
