<DOCNO> XIE20000417.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Power Sector Steps Up Technical Renovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's power industry is
undergoing a large-scale technological innovation to control
pollution, increase economic benefit and guarantee safe operation,
said a senior official today.
</P>
<P>
China will by the end of this year complete the technological
innovation of 7.5-to-8 million kilowatt medium-and low-pressure
condenser-tube generating units which have been in operation for
at least 25 years, according to Zhou Xiaoqian, assistant president
of the China State Power Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The aim is to improve the capacity of the units to meet peak-
hour demands for power, increase safety, lower consumption of
energy and protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
Referring to energy consumption, the official said that coal
consumption in power plants in China will be reduced by an average
34 grams for generating a kilowatt hour of electricity by the end
of this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, electricity voltage in major Chinese cities will
be up to standard at a rate of more than 95 percent, and the
reliability rate of power supply will reach more than 99 percent,
he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the power grids in China will
strengthen coordination in power supplies, so that the capacity of
the country's five major regional power grids and 15 provincial
power grids could reach international standards in the transfer
and control of power supplies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
