<HEADLINE> Roundup: Restructuring of China's Securities Sector (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The investment banks have also started online stock trading. It
is estimated that more than 20 investment banks have opened such
business.
</P>
<P>
Despite their increased capital, analysts, however, said China'
s investment banks are still too weak compared with their Western
counterparts, which often boast assets worth hundreds of billions
of dollars.
</P>
<P>
In practice, many investment banks now have publicly-listed
firms among their major shareholders. The above-mentioned Qinghai
Securities Co. even has 93 percent of its shares held by the
publicly-listed Qinghai Department Store Co.
</P>
<P>
Wu Xiaoqiu, head of the Financial and Securities Institute at
Renmin University, said that competition in China's investment
banking sector is still low, and large mergers and restructuring
has not yet taken off.
</P>
<P>
Wu predicted that in the coming decade, large mergers and
restructuring will greatly reduce the number of securities banks
in China and lead to the birth of super securities banks with
assets worth of tens or even hundreds of billion yuan. 
</P>
