<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Urges Further Improvement of SOEs Efficiency (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
called on State-owned enterprises (SOEs) to take concrete steps to
further restructure themselves and improve their management to lay
a solid foundation for their trans-century development.
</P>
<P>
During an study tour of Jiangxi and Hunan provinces from April
14 to 17, Wu said that the central government has mapped out
cardinal principle for SOEs' reform and development, which should
be implemented in a serious manner to ensure the realization of
the target of getting SOEs out of difficulties by the end of the
year.
</P>
<P>
"Efforts should be centered on optimizing structure, improving
quality and economic returns, and sharpening the competitive edge
of enterprises," he said.
</P>
<P>
More small factories and mines that are backward in technology,
poor in quality and serious in pollution should be shut down, and
the outdated equipment and technology eliminated, he pointed,
adding that the surplus production in some industries must be
reduced.
</P>
<P>
Greater effort should also be made in upgrading technology and
developing new products and technologies that meet market demand
and bring good economic benefits, while actively developing new
and high-tech industries, he said.
</P>
