<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Urges Further Improvement of SOEs' Efficiency (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"In the process of economic restructuring, market forces should
play a dominant role, and we should also rely on technological
progress and adopt new mechanism that meet the demand of socialist
market economy to promote the faster development of promising
industries and enterprises," Wu said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for further improvement of enterprise management,
saying that inefficient management is another major factor behind
the difficulties facing the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
He put special emphasis on the importance of improving
management of cost, capital and quality while calling for greater
effort to bring workers' enthusiasm and creativeness into full
play.
</P>
<P>
Concrete steps should be taken to establish and improve social
security system with Chinese characteristics, he said, adding that
this has a vital bearing on reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
Efficient measures must be adopted to ensure all SOEs' laid-off
and retired workers to get the full amount of living expenses and
pensions in time.
</P>
