<HEADLINE> New Xi'an Jiaotong University Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Three major universities in Xi'an,
capital of north China's Shaanxi Province, today announced that
they will merge into a new Xi'an Jiaotong University.
</P>
<P>
The three universities are Xi'an Jiaotong University, Xi'an
University of Medical Science and the Shaanxi University of
Finance.
</P>
<P>
Deputy minister of education Lu Fuyuan said that the merger
will help cultivate more talented Chinese and promote economic and
social development in China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
The new university will be run by the Ministry of Education. Xi
'an Jiaotong University was affiliated with the Ministry of
Education before the merge announcement while the other two
universities were run by the Ministry of Public Health and the
People's Bank of China respectively.
</P>
<P>
Lu expected the new Xi'an Jiaotong University to become one of
the best universities in the world.
</P>
<P>
With a faculty of about 7,400, the new university will be able
to enroll more than 23,000 full-time students. It has 64
undergraduate majors, 53 doctoral programs and 110 master degree
programs.
</P>
<P>
Xu Tongmo, president of the former Xi'an Jiaotong University,
will still hold the presidency of the newly-established university.
</P>
