<HEADLINE> Pakistan Oil Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The oil production in Pakistan
has risen from 55,128 barrels per day (bpd) to 65,100 bpd in the
recent weeks, showing an 18 percent increase, official sources
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The increase was the result of the effective efforts by the
present government, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The country's natural gas production has also been raised from
2,100 million cubic feet per day to 2,295 million cubic feet per
day.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the achievements in the energy sector, the sources
said that for the first time in the history of Pakistan,
uninterrupted gas supply was maintained to consumers during the
winter months.
</P>
<P>
Energy is one of the four key sectors which the current
Pakistani government put special priority on. The government hopes
to accelerate the privatization process in the oil and gas sector
to promote domestic energy production and thus lessen the country'
s independence on imported petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
On the privatization process, the sources said parameters and
modalities for expeditious privatization of oil and gas sector
entities have been agreed upon with the Privatization Commission.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 11 new exploration licenses were recently granted to
five exploration companies over an area of 38,385 square km
against a commitment of investment of 108 million U.S. dollars
over a period of three years, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
