<HEADLINE> New Radio Planned for Conservation of Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Plans are under way to start a
new radio station to educate people about Lake Victoria, which
borders Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda, the state-run Kenya Times
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The station will be located at Dunga Beach in Kisumu, Nyanza
Province, southwest Kenya, said Obiero Onganga, chairman of
Osienala, a non- governmental organization which deals with
conservation of the lake.
</P>
<P>
According to Onganga, the station will help inform the 30
million people residing around the lake on issues such as
conservation, pollution and fishery.
</P>
<P>
The station will also sensitize the communities around the lake
on how to use and conserve it, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the problem of overfishing, trawling, fishing using
chemicals and disposal of raw sewage into the lake must be
addressed urgently.
</P>
<P>
Those caught using chemicals to harvest fish, which is
dangerous to both the lake and human beings, would be arrested and
prosecuted according to the law, he said. 
</P>
