era of information, technology and e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
Due to the poor state of its telecommunication infrastructure,
Internet is quite a new thing to the bulk of population in
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
About 95 percent of Lagos State's records are kept manually and
their storage facilities are often in an appalling state, Tinubu
said.
</P>
<P>
It is worrisome that "it takes months for information about new
 employment, leave from service, death or retirement of clerks
could be reflected on the payroll," the governor added. 
