<HEADLINE> China's Most Populous Province Ranks First on GDP List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has become the fifth gross domestic product (GDP) giant among the
country's provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from the province's Bureau of Statistics
showed that the hinterland province's GDP has reached 456.5
billion yuan (about 55 billion US dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
The province's GDP has witnessed an average annual growth rate
of 11.7 percent over the past nine years with momentum of
infrastructure construction and industrial development.
</P>
<P>
It has been noticed that the growth rate of the agricultural
sector has declined by 10 percentage points while that of the
industrial sector up by nearly 10 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that it indicated that the economic framework of
the province has been shifting to an industrial one from the
agricultural one. It was considered a tremendous change for Henan
which was known as a traditional agricultural giant in the country.
</P>
<P>
The province is planning to attract coastal capital and
technologies with its potential advantages of resources, low cost,
and market.
</P>
<P>
Economists also pointed out that with a total population of
more than 93 million, Henan still needs to work even harder to
become an economically strong province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
