<HEADLINE> Highway to Reach Remotest Chinese Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 17 (Xinhua)-- China is to have over 330
townships and over 6,700 villages linked up by highways this year,
Vice-Minister of Communications Li Juchang announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national conference on highway construction at
this capital city of southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, Li said that China will push to make 99 percent of its
townships and 90 percent of villages accessible by highways.
