<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Producers of the upcoming Beijing
performance gala today released today the playbill for the event
scheduled for May 1 to 31.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 artists from 24 countries and regions will join
the largest-ever performance festival ever held in China, sources
with the China Performing Arts Agency (CPAA) said.
</P>
<P>
Georges Bizet's opera "Carmen" will be shown on May 1 at the
opening ceremony of the festival named "Beijing 2000."
</P>
<P>
A celebration will also take place at Culture Square near Xidan
in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, the Royal Danish Ballet, Les Ballets de
Monte Carlo, the NDR Symphony Orchestra of Hamburg, Verenigte
Buehnen Vien and the Israeli Youth Symphony Orchestra will perform
in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, many exhibitions, including those on modern
photography, Italian violins, and Yugoslavian paintings, will take
place during the gala.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Culture, the Beijing municipal government, the
State Administration of Radio, Film and Television, and the
National Tourism Administration are jointly sponsoring the event.
</P>
</TEXT>
