<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Strengthens Supervision over Milk Powder Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's annual output of milk
powder for babies has been increased from 10,000 tons to 80,000
tons over the past ten years, and supervision has recently been
strengthened to ensure quality.
</P>
<P>
A report released by the State Bureau of Quality and Technical
Supervision today shows that the quality of famous-brand Chinese
milk powder is relatively good, and producers are now equipped
with advanced equipment to ensure product quality.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the qualification rate of imported milk
powder and the milk powder produced by foreign-funded enterprises
reached 93.7 percent, according to a recent random examination.
</P>
<P>
However, quality problems were found in medium- and small-sized
enterprises, whose qualification rates were only 42.9 percent and
27.3 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the major proportion of the milk powder market share
in China is held by famous-brand Chinese and imported products.
</P>
<P>
Those enterprises failing to meet national standards will be
fined by the bureau and forced to improve quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
