<DOCNO> XIE20000417.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Japan Jointly Shoot TV Serial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Sichuan Television (SCTV),
based in Chengdu, the capital of southwest China's Sichuan
Province, and the NHK of Japan today began shooting a TV serial on
cooperation and friendship between businessmen from the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The TV serial, entitled "A Valley Reddens under the Shine of
Cherry," is the first time cooperation between the well-known
Japanese television company and a local television firm in China.
</P>
<P>
The TV drama tells about how a Japanese businessman has
developed friendly business ties with a young Chinese of ethnic
Qiang group.
</P>
<P>
The viewers will be able to have a better understanding about
the Chinese people and enjoy beautiful landscapes in China,
including the Jiuzhaigou Tourism Zone in Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
The TV serial, which is scheduled to be completed by the end of
June, is expected to be shown on the China Central Television (
CCTV), SCTV and Japanese televisions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
