<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Business Communities Asked to Forge Network for Globalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Business communities in
ASEAN countries were Monday asked to form a strong networking
capability to face the problem of economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
Making the call, Minister in Malaysian Prime Minister's
Department Bernard Dompok said that like it or not, the private
sector will have to face liberalization with foreign multinational
companies coming into their traditional markets.
</P>
<P>
"A viable option to meet this challenge is to install a coherent
and comprehensive network of business communities, each
contributing their own strengths to form a stronger and more
cohesive force," Bernama quoted him as saying at the launching of
the Malaysia Business Council of the Brunei-Indonesia-Malaysia-
Philippine East Asean Growth Area (BIMP-EAGA) in Kuching, Sarawak
State, East Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the BIMP-EAGA Malaysia Business Council's
formation was timely in view of the various onslaughts of
globalization.
</P>
<P>
The private sectors under the six-year-old BIMP-EAGA have not
fully utilized the rich resources the region was endowed with, he
said, adding they should make full use of the various forums in
BIMP-EAGA to develop business ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
