<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Monday on strong
selling following the sharp fall on Friday's Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dropped 56.
24 points or six percent to 874.97, the all-share Emas Index lost
16.67 points to 226.77, the Industrial Index dipped 108.65 points
to 1,487.47 and the Second Board Index fell 26.83 points to 249.95.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 874 to three while three counters were
unchanged and 84 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 603.602 million shares valued
at 2.274 billion ringgit (598.421 million U.S. dollars) from 282.
864 million shares valued at 1.102 billion ringgit (290 million
dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
