<HEADLINE> S. African President to Visit Zimbabwe Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki is expected to pay a state visit to strife-torn
Zimbabwe soon, the president's office confirmed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Presidential aide Parks Mankahlana said he was not sure of the
date, but a state visit was pending.
</P>
<P>
The visit has been on the cards for some time and is not as a
result of the worsening situation in Zimbabwe, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mankahlana said he would not be drawn on the significance of
the visit so near to Zimbabwe's general elections and in the midst
of the ongoing political and economic turmoil in that country.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, South African government
officials have repeatedly said that Pretoria will pursue "quiet
diplomacy" to help President Robert Mugabe solve the land question
in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Former South African president Nelson Mandela echoed this on
Monday when he told reporters in Johannesburg that any problems
South Africa has with Zimbabwe should be discussed through
diplomatic channels.
</P>
<P>
"To my own experience, South Africa would be more effective if
they dealt with the problem quietly," Mandela said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
