<HEADLINE> Putin Calls for Closer Links With Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian president-elect Vladimir
Putin on Monday called for greater British investment in his
country, saying Moscow would do everything possible to modernize
its economy.
</P>
<P>
At the start of his short visit to Britain, Putin told British
business leaders that he had a "determination to develop
cooperation with Britain."
</P>
<P>
Sustainable economic growth in Russia had become a reality and
the potential for business cooperation was "colossal", he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our main goal is to make the Russian economy attractive for
Russian and foreign investment. We will do everything to modernize
our economy," Putin told hundreds of British businessmen.
</P>
<P>
"I believe you with your business acumen can seize the
opportunities opening in the new Russia."
</P>
<P>
Putin, who is scheduled to meet Prime Minister Tony Blair later
on Monday, said Russia is solving its economic problems "very
successfully." 
</P>
</TEXT>
