<HEADLINE> Blair Meets Russia's Putin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 17 (Xinhua)-- Russian president-elect Vladimir
Putin arrived at Downing Street at Monday noon for talks with
British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are set to discuss Russia's economy, Russia-
Europe relations and the situation in the Russian breakaway
republic of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Ahead of the talks, Putin met business leaders at a seminar in
Whitehall to call for more investment in his country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the business leaders, he said new opportunities
were opening up in Russia and stressed the importance he places on
his country's integration into the world economy.
</P>
<P>
"The search for domestic sources of national growth is very
important, but the most significant factor for us is the
integration of Russia into the world economy. We have to restore
the confidence of foreign investors and reduce the fiscal burden
of Russian policy," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sustainable economic growth in Russia had become a reality and
the potential for business cooperation was "colossal", he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our main goal is to make the Russian economy attractive for
Russian and foreign investment. We will do everything to modernize
our economy."
</P>
<P>
During his 24-hour visit to Britain, Putin will also lay a
wreath at the Soviet War Memorial at the Imperial War Museum in
London and meet Queen Elizabeth II. 
</P>
</TEXT>
