<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Asian Taekwondo Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, China, April 17 (Xinhua) - Hong Kong of China will
host the 14th Asian Taekwondo Championships on May 13-16, the Hong
Kong Taekwondo Association (HKTWDA), annouced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The four-day competitions feature eight male and female
divisions respectively. About 40 countries and regions were
invited by HKTWDA.
</P>
<P>
There are 21 countries and regions, such as China, South Korea,
Japan, Chinese Taipei, Kazakstan, Guam, Vietnam, Australia, have
confirmed their participation in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Taekwondo is one of the most popular sports in Hong Kong as
over 50,000 people are enjoying fun in it.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong won a silver medal in the event in 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
