<HEADLINE> Monte Carlo Open Delayed for Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- There would be only one match to be
played on Monday in the 2.95-million-U.S.-dollar Monte Carlo Open
as the rain disrupted the first-day play of the tennis tournament
in Monte Carlo, Monaco.
</P>
<P>
The sole match to start was between Norwegian Christian Ruud
and Swede Andreas Vinciguerra on court two, which possesses a
removable roof.
</P>
<P>
The matches, including the last game of the day between Russian
Yevgeny Kafelnikov and Czech Daniel Vacek, were expected to start
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Americans Andre Agassi and Pete Sampras had pulled out of the
event for injuries. 
</P>
