<HEADLINE> Ruud Wins First Match in Rain-hit Monte Carlo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian qualifier Christian Ruud
won the only match of the first day play in the 2.95-million-U.S.-
dollar Monte Carlo Open, which was hit by rain on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rain delayed 16 first-round singles matches to
Tuesday, but Ruud's game against Sweden's Andreas Vinciguerra
could go on on court two, which possesses a removable roof.
</P>
<P>
Ruud, a quarter-finalist in Monte Carlo, Monaco, in 1997, won
the match with 4-6, 7-5, 6-1 in one hour and 56 minutes. 
</P>
