<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quarterly Interbank Forex Transactions Up In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Interbank foreign
exchange trading volume reached 9.598 billion US dollars during
the first quarter of the year, according to the Shanghai-based
China Foreign Exchange Trade System.
</P>
<P>
This means an average 155 million US dollars were traded for
each of the 62 trading days in the three-month period, a 43.6-
percent rise on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The total volume included 9.38 billion US dollars, 797 million
Hong Kong dollars, and 12.299 billion Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The quarter's weighted average exchange rate of the US dollar
hit 8.2786 yuan, with the exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar
averaged at 1.0636 yuan, and the yuan-yen rate standing at 7.7287:
100, down 0.2101 points from the average for the fourth quarter of
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
