<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clean-Up of Polluted River in Shanghai Insured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI April 17 (Xinhua) -- The first phase of a project to
clear Suzhou River, a seriously polluted tributary passing through
Shanghai, has been recently insured for 3.5 billion yuan by three
insurance companies against all construction risks and third-party
liabilities.
</P>
<P>
Half of the coverage is insured by the local Dazhong Insurance
Company, with the rest shared by the Shanghai branches of the Ping
'an and China Pacific insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
As a major tributary of the Huangpu River, the 120-km-long
Suzhou River has been seriously polluted by sewage from industrial
production and waste water from the daily life of local residents,
posing an increasingly serious threat to the local people.
</P>
<P>
The local government has begun to clean up the river in phases.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
