<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Maintain Cotton Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The purchase price of cotton this
year on China's domestic market will remain at 400 yuan (about 49
US dollars) per 50 kilograms, basically the same as last year,
according to the State Price Information Center.
</P>
<P>
The opening of cotton market since last September brought down
cotton prices by a wide margin, and statistics show that the
average price was 380 yuan per 50 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
However, exports and domestic sales increases of cotton
products as well as a recovering world market pushed up prices to
420 yuan per 50 kilograms during the first two months this year.
</P>
<P>
Large cotton stockpiles in China and increased cotton acreage
in the world's major cotton producers including the United States
and several Central Asian countries will possibly lead to a fall
in cotton prices, the center said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
