<DOCNO> XIE20000417.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows to Tighten Control over Medicine Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China will take effective
measures to strengthen supervision over the quality of medicine
and stem fake products from flowing into the market, the State
Drug Administration (SDA) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The SDA, China's drug-quality watchdog, also announced that it
has suspended seven pharmaceutical plants from producing seven
kinds of products for quality reasons.
</P>
<P>
A sample survey of 8,501 kinds of medicine revealed that 754
failed to meet state standards. Compared with 2.7 percent
substandard drug products from pharmaceutical plants, about 12
percent of the drugs available in drug stores or used in hospitals
were of poor quality.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted in the first quarter of this year by
the National Institute for Control of Pharmaceutical and
Biological Products and its local branches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
