<HEADLINE> Personal Computer Sales on Increase in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 835,000 units of
personal computers (PCs) were estimated to be sold this year
against a total of 680,000 units sold in Malaysia last year.
</P>
<P>
However, computer usage in Malaysia is still in the initial
stage and this means that the opportunities for PC sales are great,
Bernama news agency said Monday.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that about 4.0 percent of households in
Malaysia own at least one PC and there are only 45 PCs for every 1,
000 Malaysians.
</P>
<P>
It is also estimated that the saturation stage would be reached
in 2004/05 as it normally takes about five years for a country to
have 10 percent of the households owning a PC each.
</P>
<P>
There are about 700,000 register Internet users in Malaysia in
1999 and by the year 2003, one conservative estimate puts the
projected figure to be at 1.3 million users.
</P>
<P>
Under the Seventh Malaysia Plan (1996-2000), the Malaysian
government allocated 2.3 billion ringgit (605.263 million U.S.
dollars) for the government computerization program compared with
1.4 billion ringgit (368.421 million U.S. dollars) spent under the
Sixth Malaysia Plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
