<HEADLINE> Riot Kills Two in Indonesia's North Sulawesi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were killed
and dozens of houses were set ablaze in a riot which took place in
Poso city, Indonesia's Central Sulawesi province, a report
reaching here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Antara news agency reported that the riot took place on Sunday
and continued to Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The riot was sparked by a quarrel between youths from Lombogia
village and Lawanga village (in Poso city). But then, they (both
sides) started using ethnic sentiments," the agency said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted witnesses as saying that the number of houses and
buildings which have been destroyed by angry mobs reached more
than ten units.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the regional police Captain Rudi Suprapto said
that the police at the movement can not give detailed information
on the riot.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that until Monday morning schools and shops in
the area were still closed and economic activities were totally
paralyzed while, "security officers keep trying to control the two
warring groups." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
