<DOCNO> XIE20000417.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Western Development: A Huge Business Opportunity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China's western development
strategy is a huge business opportunity, said Chen Jinhua,
chairman of the China Enterprise Confederation, here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the on-going China Business Summit 2000, Chen said
business contacts involving 100 billion yuan (about 12.9 billion
US dollars) had been signed during a recent east-west trade fair,
which shows the irresistible attraction of China's western region.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Planning Commission will announce a
detailed plan for China's western development before the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
China is concentrating on infrastructure construction,
ecological environment improvement, economic restructuring,
science and education development, and further opening up.
</P>
<P>
This year's ten large construction projects in the western
region, which involve railways, highways, urban elevated railways,
airports, water conservancy, and natural gas pipelines, will
provide great opportunities for investors worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Chen pointed out that China's strategy will help expand
domestic demand and guarantee steady growth of the economy. The
strategy will also be very helpful for promoting social stability
and the harmonious development of all provinces.
</P>
<P>
He said that low labor and land costs in western China are very
attractive, and foreign investors are welcome.
</P>
<P>
China's western region cover 56 percent of the country's land
area and has 23 percent of China's population. But its per-capita
gross domestic product is only 60 percent of the national average.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
