<HEADLINE> Vice-Chairwoman of NPC Standing Committee Meets Brazilian MP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairwoman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) He Luli said
here Monday afternoon that China's NPC wishes to expand exchanges
with the Brazilian Congress at all levels.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Chairwoman told Freitas Neto, senator of the Brazilian
Congress and head of a delegation of the Liberal Front Party of
Brazil, that China holds that contacts between the congresses of
the two countries will help increase understanding between the two
peoples, as well as the development of the economic, technological
and cultural sectors of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Brazil established diplomatic relations in August
1974, and the two countries have constantly expanded their
friendly relations over the past decades, He noted.
</P>
<P>
"As two large developing countries, China and Brazil should
further push forward their friendly cooperative relationship,
which will be good for the two peoples, and good for world peace
and stability," she said.
</P>
<P>
Neto said that his party hopes to strengthen its relations with
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and further develop friendly
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Neto and his delegation are on a week-long visit to China.
</P>
</TEXT>
