<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Returns Home From Overseas Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid returns home on Monday from his ten-day overseas trip.
</P>
<P>
The president along with his entourage including local
journalists arrived here at about 12;20 a.m. (local time) from
China's Hong Kong, the last stopover of the president's tour which
also brought him to South Africa, Mexico, Cuba and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Wahid was welcomed by Vice-president Megawati Soekarnoputeri at
Halim Perdana Kusuma airport, along with some cabinet members.
</P>
<P>
During his overseas trip Wahid attended the G-77 summit in Cuba
where he gave his support for more constructive cooperation among
the G-77 members.
</P>
<P>
The President was also believed to have played a significant
role particularly in influencing donor countries to meet the
country's request in foreign debt rescheduling.
</P>
<P>
During the Paris Club II meeting (April 12-13), the government
of Indonesia was successful in asking for its foreign debt
rescheduling mounting to 5.8 billion U.S. dollars from the donors,
greater than the 2.1 billion U.S. dollars it had expected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
