<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Most Wanted Drug Suspect Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's most wanted drug
suspect has been arrested in Kenya and brought back to the north
town of Moshi to answer charges of unlawful possession of drugs
worth more than 7 billion shillings (about 8.75 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Guardian newspaper Monday quoted police in the northern
Kilimanjaro Region as confirming at the weekend that Focus Kisaka
was arrested last week in Nairobi with the cooperation of
Interpol.
</P>
<P>
The suspect has been on a wanted list by police for the past
four years after a consignment of cannabis resin was impounded
near his home on February 6, 1996 at Kirua Vunjo in Moshi
Kilimanjaro Region, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
