<HEADLINE> French Policeman Arrested for Killing Arab Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A French police officer was
arrested Sunday evening for suspected intentional manslaughter
after he shot dead an Arab man in the northern city of Lille, the
Agence France-Presse reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The police officer shot dead Riad Hamlaoui, an Algerian of 25
years old, when the latter was reportedly trying to steal a car
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The death of Hamlaoui caused violent confrontation Saturday
night and Sunday morning between protesters and police in the
southern district of Lille, where there is a large northern
African minority population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
