<HEADLINE> Ferry Sinks in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A passenger vessel sank early
Monday morning when en route to Bantangas province in the northern
Philippines after hitting a hard object, said a TV report.
</P>
<P>
According to the local ABS-CBN television, all 85 passengers
and seven crew on vessel Viva Penafrancia were declared safe after
two ships came to their rescue.
</P>
<P>
However, the cargo aboard the ship was not recovered, said the
TV report.
</P>
<P>
This is the second sea tragedy in the country in less than a
week. At least 138 people died when cargo vessel Arlahada capsized
last Wednesday off Sulu Province in the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The authorities estimated that Arlahada was carrying more than
200 passengers when it was actually fit for only 50. A total of 79
people aboard the ferry cargo have been rescued and rescuers are
continuing to search for more survivors. 
</P>
