<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Mediates Congo Row </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has brought together rival cliques within Prof. Ernest Wamba dia
Wamba's RCD- Kisangani rebel group of the Democratic Republic of
the Congo for talks to bridge their differences.
</P>
<P>
The New Vision daily reported on Monday that the five-hour
talks, which was held at the State House and ended at about 1.00
a.m. local time on Sunday, had Wamba dia Wamba facing his
deputies, Mbusa Nyamwisi, the prime minister and John Tibasima
Atenyi.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted sources as saying that the talks will
resume on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Recent press reports and security sources said that the two
Wamba deputies were operating almost independent of the
scholar-turned rebel chief.
</P>
<P>
The sharp differences between the rebel leaders had a lot to do
with poor accountability for funds from minerals and customs
collections, sources said.
</P>
<P>
There was really nothing serious dividing these people, said
Col. Kahinda Otafiire, the presidential adviser on the DRC, who
also attended the meeting. He added that there was a communication
breakdown between them which enemy propaganda later used to try to
split them.
</P>
<P>
The talks have been going on well, and the issues that brought
 misunderstandings are being addressed, said Tibasima. 
</P>
