<HEADLINE> Zambian Media to Receive UN Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will receive assistance
from the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa (UNECA) to
improve its information network, according to Information and
Broadcasting Minister Newstead Zimba.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at Lusaka international airport from a
regional meeting in the Namibian capital Windhoek on Sunday, the
minister said both electronic and print media in Zambia would
benefit greatly from the assistance.
</P>
<P>
Monday's Times of Zambia newspaper quoted UNECA director Robert
Okello, who also attended the regional meeting, as saying that
experts would be coming to Zambia to work with the information
ministry on the implementation of some of the ideas discussed at
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Information technology is the driving force behind the process
of globalization, and electronic and print media are to benefit
from the latest information technology in the global world, Okello
said. 
