<HEADLINE> White Commercial Farmer Shot Dead in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A white commercial farmer in
Zimbabwe was shot dead on Saturday, allegedly by war veterans who
abducted him following a clash between his workers and
ex-combatants occupying his farm, the daily Herald reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted police spokesman Chief Superintendent Wayne
Bvudzijena as saying on Sunday that the victim, David Stevens
(50), of Arizona Farm, was shot between the eyes and shoulder
blades.
</P>
<P>
His body was discovered at Dapandare River Bridge, southeast of
Murehwa, Sunday morning by a police search team using
helicopters, Bvudzijena said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, events leading to Stevens' death
started when he armed himself with a gun and instructed his
workers to arm themselves as well.
</P>
<P>
They allegedly attacked and injured 14 of the 35 war veterans,
who have been occupying the farm since February, using spears,
hoes, sticks and stones.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Britain Sunday summoned Zimbabwe's High
 Commissioner in London Simbarashe Mumbengegwi, demanding an end
to farm invasions in the African country.
</P>
<P>
The killers must be found and charged, said British Foreign
Secretary Robin Cook while speaking in India. 
</P>
