<HEADLINE> Guangdong's External Trade Sees Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province witnessed rapid growth in its foreign trade in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The total value of Guangdong's imports and exports surged an
year-on-year 36.6 percent to reach 36.08 billion US dollars during
the January-March period, accounting for 36.7 percent of China's
total.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that its export value was 19.99 billion US
dollars, up 42.7 percent, while the import value hit 16.09 billion
US dollars, an increase of 29.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local experts cited economic recovery in Japan, the Republic of
Korea and Singapore as a major factor behind the rapid foreign
trade growth of Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
They predict that the province's external trade will continue
to rise in the second quarter of this year.  
