<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed sharply lower here Monday because of the severe declines of
the Wall Street at the end of last week.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 97 points lower at 1,974 with a turnover
of 97.2 million NZ dollars (48.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, AMP fell 70 cents to 1,830 cents, Sky
TV 50 to 415 cents, Telecom 47 to 863 cents, Telstra 45 to 855
cents, and Fletcher Energy 40 to 460 cents.
</P>
<P>
Colonial lost 23 cents to 1,000 cents, the Warehouse 21 to 419
cents, Contact Energy 9 to 243 cents, Fletcher Building 6 to 199
cents, and Fletcher Forests 5 to 66 cents.
</P>
<P>
