<HEADLINE> Int'l Giftware Exhibition Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The event features a total of 3,446 exhibitors from 41
countries and regions around the world, 3,033 companies at the
Gift and House Fair, and 413 at the Premium Show.
</P>
<P>
Among the exhibitors, 35 percent come from areas outside Hong
Kong, including delegates of the 17 group pavilions from Australia,
China's mainland, France, Germany, India, Indonesia, Italy, South
Korea, Macao, Malaysia, South Africa, Taiwan Province, Thailand,
the United Kingdom, the United States and new groups from Japan
and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The four-day fair, organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development
Council together with the Hong Kong Exporters' Association, offers
an effective marketing platform to the giftware industry and will
propel Hong Kong's rise as the premier sourcing center in the
region, Jeffrey Lam, chairman of the fair's organizing committee,
said at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
This year's highlights include high-end lifestyle products from
24 select exhibitors, featuring branded and designer items from
Canada, Germany, Hong Kong, Italy, Spain, Switzerland and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The event is sectioned according to product categories,
covering gifts, consumer electronics and electrical appliances,
houseware, kitchenware and tableware, as well as carnival and
Christmas decorations. 
