JAKARTA -- Indonesian consumers have confidence that the
country's economy is on the rise and the economic conditions will
improve over the next six months, a local newspapers reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
For the first time since October 1999, the percentage of
consumers claiming current conditions were good outweighed the
percentage claiming otherwise, the Jakarta Post daily Monday
reported quoting the findings of the country's survey institute,
the Danareksa Research Institute. (Indonesia-Economic Outlook)
