<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pacers Win First Eastern Conference Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indiana Pacers won a hard
away game against the Detroit Pistons on Sunday, cruising to a 112-
101 victory and their first Eastern Conference title.
</P>
<P>
Jalen Rose scored 14 of his 20 points in the fourth quarter,
giving Indiana a 92-80 cushion with nine minutes to play, and the
Pacers (54-26) will enter the playoffs as the top seed in the East
for the first time as they still seek their first NBA title.
</P>
<P>
Reggie Miller scored 21 points and Rik Smits added 14 for the
Pacers.
</P>
<P>
In Phoenix, Karl Malone joined Kareem Abdul-Jabbar and Wilt
Chamberlain to become the third player in NBA history to record 31,
000 points, scoring 32 with 15 rebounds, as the Utah Jazz beat the
Phoenix Suns with a 96-82 victory.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, Eddie Jones scored 23 of his 25 points in the first
three quarters as the Charlotte Hornets celebrated a 105-102
victory over the Boston Celtics.
</P>
<P>
The Hornets still trailed fourth-place Philadelphia by one game
for home-court advantage in the first round of the playoffs, which
begin next weekend.
</P>
<P>
In Houston, Gary Payton played all 48 minutes and scored a
career-high 43 points as the Seattle SuperSonics moved into a
seventh-place tie in the Western Conference with a 121-112 triumph
over the Houston Rockets.
</P>
<P>
Seattle (44-36) is deadlocked with Sacramento for seventh in
the West heading into Tuesday's showdown at Arco Arena. If the
Sonics lose, they will face the top-seeded Los Angeles Lakers in
the first round.
</P>
<P>
In Los Angeles, the Lakers fought off a stiff challenge from
the Minnesota Timberwolves for a 101-95 victory as Shaquille O'
Neal had 33 points, 14 rebounds and eight assists and Kobe Bryant
added 25 points and 10 assists.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers has won 14 of its last 15 games.
</P>
<P>
In Miami, the Heat rallied from an eight-point deficit and
posted a 95-84 win over the Orlando Magic for its fourth straight
division title.
</P>
<P>
In Toronto, the Raptors erased a 15-point fourth-quarter
deficit and escaped with a thrilling 85-84 victory over the
Chicago Bulls, the worst team in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, the Hawks snapped their nine-game losing streak
with a 104-101 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, the Mavericks defeated the Vancouver Grizzlies 114-
106 to clinch a winning home record this season, while in Portland
the Trail Blazers defeated the Sacramento Kings 102-95. 
</P>
</TEXT>
