<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Arrested for Panicking Public in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Three local people in the Thai-
Myanmar border areas were arrested early this month for plotting
to panic the public during the just-ended three-day Water Festival
and to perpetrate subversive activities at busy places in the
capital of Yangon, a local newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar Monday,
the three persons, said to have been sent by a group called the "
People's Power-21st Century (PP-21)" based in Thailand, were
arrested with explosive powder and electric detonators by the
Myanmar Defense Services Intelligence units in Myawaddy and
Kyondoe, Myanmar border towns opposite to Thailand, on April 1 and
11.
</P>
<P>
Organized with members of the All Burma Students' Democratic
Front and Kayin National Union, two of the anti-government armed
groups operating on the Thai-Myanmar border, the PP-21 group is
said to have been formed in Thailand's Chiangmai in 1998,
financially backed by a non-governmental organization from Norway
named "Political Defiance Burma."
</P>
<P>
The authorities are taking action against the three, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
