<HEADLINE> Revenue of China's Pharmaceutical Industry Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) ---- The sales revenue of China's
pharmaceutical industry grew 13.7 percent to reach 116.6 billion
yuan in 1999, according to latest statistics from the bureau of
pharmaceutical industry.
</P>
<P>
 The profits of pharmaceutical plants across the country
totaled 168 million yuan, 21 percent more than in the same period
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
 The 15 major pharmaceutical plants surveyed reported an
average profit growth of 29.55 percent in November, 1999 higher
than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The sales profit rate of the pharmaceutical industry in the
western areas was higher than in the eastern areas, with the
national average reaching seven percent in Jan-Nov 1999, a rise of
0.4 percentage point over the same period of 1998. The rate in the
western area ran as high as 10.13 percent; that in the central
area, 7.79 percent; that in the eastern area, 6.20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the losses of pharmaceutical enterprises were
reduced by a big margin in the Jan-Nov period of 1999, with the
number of loss-making enterprises making up 35.2 percent of the
country's total, 1.1 percentage points lower than in the same
period of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
