<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Martinez to Win Amelia Island Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the United
States defeated Spain's Conchita Martinez to win a WTA tennis
tournament in Amelia Island, Florida, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Seles' 6-3, 6-2 victory was her 18th win in 19 career meetings
with the fourth-seeded Martinez, including a perfect 7-0 on clay
and all straight-set triumphs.
</P>
<P>
Seles never gave the Spaniard a chance to gain any momentum
while Martinez was heavily dependent on Seles' mistakes to stay in
the match.
</P>
<P>
It was the second tournament victory this season for Seles, who
also captured the hardcourt title at Oklahoma City in February.
</P>
