<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Tumor Removed From Woman's Stomach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A benign tumor weighing 5 kilograms
has been removed from a woman's belly in the Xijing Hospital in
this capital city of northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The woman surnamed Liu has been discharged from the hospital
and is now in good condition, according to doctors. This is the
100th case that the hospital has removed similar tumors.
</P>
<P>
Liu is a nurse at the Jingyang County Hospital in Shaanxi. She
felt a lump on her belly seven years ago. The lump continued to
grow and she looked like a pregnant woman.
</P>
<P>
She had had four operations previously in other hospitals, but
the tumor had not been completely removed. In mid-March this year,
surgeons in the Xijing Hospital completely removed the huge tumor
for her.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said such tumors showed no early symptoms. In most cases,
the tumor is found only when it has grown big enough to affect the
functions of other organs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
