<HEADLINE> Threatened Marsupial Found in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 17 (Xinhua) --Australian Environment Minister
Iain Evans announced that six threatened Australian marsupial
named as Sandhill Dunnart have been found by a local naturalist on
South Australia's Eyre Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The AAP said that it was the first sighting of the carnivorous
marsupial in the area since about 1969.
</P>
<P>
According to AAP, The Sandhill Dunnart, which is a little
larger than a house mouse and can grow up to 25 cm, is more
commonly found in the remote sand dune and desert plain country of
the Great Victorian Desert in South Australia and Western
Australia.
</P>
<P>
Evans said the discovery was good news for the ongoing efforts
to increase it's numbers, the AAP reported. 
</P>
