<HEADLINE> Australian Economy Remains Solid: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Australian Prime Minister John
Howard issued an optimistic statement Monday on the world economy
after Friday night's stockmarket plunge on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
He told ABC Radio that The fundamentals of the Australian
economy are rock solid and the world economy, looked at in a
generic way, is now stronger and has been growing at a very
powerful rate now for longer than at any time for the last 20 or
30 years.
</P>
<P>
The economic trend in Australia depends largely on the U.S.
economy and it has grown for more than 100 successive months
drawing support from the strong U.S. economy.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. economy was strong and Australia's just as strong, the
Prime Minister said, adding that Asian economies had rebounded,
Europe was improving and Japan was showing signs of recovery too.
</P>
<P>
