<HEADLINE> Palestinian Students Clash with Israeli Soldiers on "Captive Day" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Several Palestinian students were
injured when a demonstration marking the "Captive Day" turned to a
violent clash with the Israeli forces in the West Bank city of
Bethlehem on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces resorted to violence to stop the march of
Palestinian students around Belal Mosque, north Bethlehem, the
Palestinian News Agency (WAFA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces fired rubber bullets and tear gas bombs at
the students. Many students suffered injuries, coma and
suffocation. Eyewitnesses said four students sustained bullet
injuries after they stoned the Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
All the Palestinian towns in the West Bank and Gaza Strip
witnessed demonstration in solidarity with about 1,600 of the
Palestinian detainees in the Israeli jails.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the Palestinian National Authority Yasser
Arafat told reporters here this afternoon after his meeting with
Omani Foreign Minister Yousef Bin Alawi Bin Abdullah that he always
stands by the Palestinian detainees.
</P>
<P>
Speaker of the Palestinian Legislative Council Ahmed Qureia was
quoted by WAFA as saying that the detainee issue is on top of the
PLC priorities. He condemned Israel for procrastinating the
implementation of the peace accords that provide clearly for
releasing all the Palestinian detainees.
</P>
<P>
Since the signing of the Sharm el-Sheikh Memorandum with the
Palestinian last September, Israel has released 400 Palestinian
political detainees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
