<HEADLINE> Annan Hopes Congo Explosion Not to hamper Peace process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Monday expressed the hope that the airport explosion of
the Democratic Republic of Congo (DDR) would not hamper the peace
process in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by his spokesman's office, Annan
conveyed his sympathies to the government and people of the DDR
and his deepest condolences to the families of the deceased.
</P>
<P>
Annan hoped the incident would not affect implementation of a
ceasefire and a disengagement of forces agreed on earlier this
month by combatants.
</P>
<P>
Annan said the United Nations remained committed to the
earliest implementation of this agreement as well as to the
provision of humanitarian assistance.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, over 100 people died in a
series of large explosions at Kinshasa's Jdjili airport Friday.
Airport facilities were damaged and four planes were destroyed.
</P>
</TEXT>
