<HEADLINE> S. Africa Wants to Develop Military Ties with Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is to establish
a military relationship with Nigeria to enhance stability on the
African continent, South African military intelligence head said
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The chief of defense intelligence of the South African National
Defence Forces Lieutenant-General Johannes Notau, who arrived in
Nigeria on Sunday for a five-day official visit, said in the
capital Abuja that South Africa is determined to enter into areas
of military cooperation with Nigeria to foster understanding,
South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's chief of defense intelligence Rear Admiral Joseph
Ajayi said Nigeria hopes its military intelligence instructors can
be offered courses at South Africa's Intelligence Training Centre.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have had almost no military links before.
</P>
<P>
Neither Nigeria nor South Africa have become members of the
African Crisis Response Initiative sponsored by the United States,
which is meant to mobilize forces from African countries to
intervene in areas of conflict.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
