<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rebound Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 17 (Xinhua)-- Wall Street stocks Bounced back
sharply Monday after a jolt last week.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 276.74 at 10,582.51.
The index lost 805.71 points last week.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 217.87 at 3,
539.16, trimming last week's heavy losses of 1,125.16 points.
</P>
<P>
The indexes rose as investors moved in the market to buy big-
name stocks. Strong profit reports on the first quarter of the
year from Ford Motor, Citigroup and Merrill Lynch also encouraged
investors.
</P>
<P>
Investors dumped their stocks last Friday in fears of rising
inflation after the Labor Department reported that Consumer Price
Index rose sharply in March. The Dow index fell 617.78 points
while the Nasdaq index dropped 355.49 points on that day. The
Friday jolt also shook the financial markets around the world.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators Monday were mostly higher. The
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 44.88 at 1,401.44.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 8.72 at 620.21 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 5.45 at 459.18. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 9.00 at 848.97.
</P>
<P>
Declining stocks outnumbered advancers by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,725 down, 1,310 up and 408
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 1.195 billion shares from 1.251 billion
on the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
